OL,3,CExperts solve mystery of glass window
OL,4,Cshards anonymously returned to abbey
OL,6,FThe ingredients used to make the glass
OL,7,F` lead, potassium, arsenic and sulphur
OL,8,F` meant Dr Kennedy was able to
OL,9,Fdetermine that it was made between the
OL,10,F1870s and the 1930s.
OL,12,FVivienne Kelly, a PhD student
OL,13,Fsupervised by Dr Kennedy and an expert
OL,14,Fstained-glass conservator who
OL,15,Fspecialises in 19th and 20th century
OL,16,Fglass, was also involved.
OL,18,FThe Glasgow School of Art graduate
OL,19,Ffocused on studying four large pieces
OL,20,Fto identify the imagery.
